76561197992229015,Not Recommended,260330,25988263,"Posted: 11 October, 2016",all,Dire,"This is basically lemmings...with sheep, but unfortunately it's not nearly as good. The graphics are muddy and ugly. Well, it's understandable, cause you're in a butcher factory or whatever, but I mean they're really detracting from the actual gameplay. The camera is sluggish. The game runs poorly on a modern rig and the overall gameplay is just not satisfying enough to carry it forward.Your task, just as in lemmings, is to guide as many sheep to the exit, while sacrificing some on the way. For that you have various tools. Sorry, did I say various tools? Nah. Actually there are only 3 (jumping sheep, flying sheep and exploding sheep). The rest of the kit consists of ""blocks"", i.e. your sheep can be used as stepping stones (1, 2 or 3) like a staircase or as a soft block (2 sheep high), which means only flying sheep can cross over that. You can also release your sheep from stair or blocking duty. That is it. That is the game. At least that's what it's been for the first 10 or so levels. You get access to all the tools from the start.To actually use these blocks you have to gather them in the level. The levels consist of different traps and teleporters, walls and gaps. Honestly, it's again, boring. There's nothing to really differentiate the levels from each other. They look and feel the same. Maybe this gets better later on, but if your game doesn't progress anywhere after 1 hour it's not worth my time anymore. There are also boss levels...the first one is you being chased by a giant ""something"" on wheels. Your sheep will die...horribly...and bloodily. And I guess this is the main selling point of the game. Since it is enough to get even a single sheep through to beat the level there's not much strategy involved, unless you want to go score attack...which with the amount of levels in there (a ton) sounds like work and not fun.The controls are also kinda wonky, especially since you can't use the pause mode to actually plan stuff. In Lemmings you could assign individual lemmings to important roles. Here it's more like ""paste that♥♥♥♥♥♥over every sheep to make them fly"". Personally, I find this game to be dull and dreary. Maybe get it at a steep discount. 18 bucks is way too much for the level of polish you get here, though it does offer a decent amount of levels. Too bad the levels aren't interesting."
